01:09:46.970 --> 01:09:48.270
Obviously, where the issue

01:09:48.270 --> 01:09:51.910
at hand is historically
unprecedented one cannot rely

01:09:51.910 --> 01:09:55.450
on the classical schools
of law for solutions even

01:09:55.450 --> 01:09:57.950
through extensions by analogy.

01:09:57.950 --> 01:10:02.580
Ijtihad in this context becomes
an obligation by default.

01:10:02.580 --> 01:10:05.320 position:56%
This is actually quite
straightforward from the perspective

01:10:05.320 --> 01:10:07.460
of the classical tradition.

01:10:07.460 --> 01:10:10.820
Modern Muslims, however, often
invents a certain diffidence

01:10:10.820 --> 01:10:14.360
or even hostility towards Ijtihad.

01:10:14.360 --> 01:10:17.840
This is less a question
though of Ijtihad's status

01:10:17.840 --> 01:10:21.230
as a legitimate approach
to sharia than it is a sort

01:10:21.230 --> 01:10:25.630 position:56%
of resentment towards the sense
that it is largely western modernity

01:10:25.630 --> 01:10:29.400
that is generating the need
for Ijtihad to begin with.

01:10:29.400 --> 01:10:32.990
With time of course, such
feelings can only dissipate.

01:10:32.990 --> 01:10:37.750
In fact, I would hazard that a good
deal of Ijtihad is likely to emerge

01:10:37.750 --> 01:10:43.030 position:56%
out of those Muslim communities from
whom western reality is not imposed

01:10:43.030 --> 01:10:44.880
or sensed as being imposed,

01:10:44.880 --> 01:10:48.130
but is rather the only
reality they have ever known.

01:10:48.130 --> 01:10:53.210 position:56%
But what may be difficult to imagine
in the present moment this points

01:10:53.210 --> 01:10:56.720
to the importance of western
Muslim communities and the future

01:10:56.720 --> 01:11:00.030
or to the future of Islamic law.

01:11:00.030 --> 01:11:05.400
Now having said this much, Ijtihad
remains limited in its utility.

01:11:05.400 --> 01:11:07.700
For many of the most
problematic features

01:11:07.700 --> 01:11:10.340
of Islamic law are
precisely those rules

01:11:10.340 --> 01:11:14.740
that the classical tradition has
upheld for literally centuries.

01:11:14.740 --> 01:11:17.750
Of course, one could
argue and many Muslims do

01:11:17.750 --> 01:11:21.540
that Ijtihad is also
the solution here.

01:11:21.540 --> 01:11:24.510
We simply need to go back
and reinterpret the sources

01:11:24.510 --> 01:11:27.480
in order to produce new rules.

01:11:27.480 --> 01:11:32.140
Ultimately, however, this takes us
back to the problem of authority

01:11:32.140 --> 01:11:36.520
for like it or not the classical
tradition will likely retain much

01:11:36.520 --> 01:11:39.570
more authority than any
contemporary individual

01:11:39.570 --> 01:11:42.200
or movement could hope to muster.

01:11:42.200 --> 01:11:46.390 position:56%
Nor are we guaranteed that new rules
will necessarily be better rules

01:11:46.390 --> 01:11:50.180
as we see in the case of so-called
extremist movements today.

01:11:50.180 --> 01:11:53.380
Nor will contemporary
interpretations necessarily win the

01:11:53.380 --> 01:11:56.380
day by simply declaring
themselves to be right

01:11:56.380 --> 01:11:59.560
and classical rules to be wrong.

01:11:59.560 --> 01:12:02.520
This recognition, however, of
the basic authority wielded

01:12:02.520 --> 01:12:07.100
by the classical tradition need
not bind us to the perspective

01:12:07.100 --> 01:12:12.270
or to the perspectives of the
classical jurists themselves

01:12:12.270 --> 01:12:15.210 position:56%
for there was an important
distinction between their statements

01:12:15.210 --> 01:12:18.770
of law and their assessments
of fact.

01:12:18.770 --> 01:12:22.450
On this distinction classical
rules can be right in terms

01:12:22.450 --> 01:12:24.790
of their legal substance
and it is not my contention

01:12:24.790 --> 01:12:27.660
that they're necessarily
right, but they could be right.

01:12:27.660 --> 01:12:31.690
While at the same time being
wrong when the attempt is

01:12:31.690 --> 01:12:36.300
to apply these rules to change
the factual circumstances.

01:12:36.300 --> 01:12:40.120
Recognizing this feature
renders any number of the rules

01:12:40.120 --> 01:12:43.710
on the books totally
obsolete and inapplicable

01:12:43.710 --> 01:12:46.740
to a modern set of circumstances.

01:12:46.740 --> 01:12:51.890
Classical deliberations were not
theoretical, but rather practical.

01:12:51.890 --> 01:12:56.590
They aim to address the concrete
everyday realities of society.

01:12:56.590 --> 01:13:02.940
As such, almost all classical legal
conclusions include an admixture

01:13:02.940 --> 01:13:07.230
of law that is the jurists'
interpretations of the sources

01:13:07.230 --> 01:13:10.820
and fact of the practical
circumstances the jurists were

01:13:10.820 --> 01:13:13.150
seeking to adjudicate.

01:13:13.150 --> 01:13:16.840
While the strictly legal dimension
of these rulings might be assumed

01:13:16.840 --> 01:13:18.140
to entail an element

01:13:18.140 --> 01:13:21.710
of transcendence being presumably
grounded in some interpretation

01:13:21.710 --> 01:13:25.760
of scripture the factual
dimensions could not.

01:13:25.760 --> 01:13:29.930
To take one example, based on
prophetic precedent contracts

01:13:29.930 --> 01:13:34.600
of sale generally entail an implied
warranty with a specified amount

01:13:34.600 --> 01:13:38.050
of time to check the
product's integrity.

01:13:38.050 --> 01:13:42.780
How much time, however, dependent
on the jurists' factual assessment

01:13:42.780 --> 01:13:47.700
of what prevailing circumstances
dictated as fair and reasonable.

01:13:47.700 --> 01:13:52.050
In that light the maximum time
allowed for real estate was set

01:13:52.050 --> 01:13:56.980
at 36 days and this is the maximum
warranty period that one will find

01:13:56.980 --> 01:14:01.390
in classical laws on classical
manuals on Islamic law.

01:14:01.390 --> 01:14:04.360
But this 36 day allowance
was clearly not a matter

01:14:04.360 --> 01:14:09.770
of permanent law even if the rule
[inaudible] implied warranties was.

01:14:09.770 --> 01:14:11.320
And in modern context

01:14:11.320 --> 01:14:14.870
where commercial real estate is
extremely complicated this period

01:14:14.870 --> 01:14:19.680 position:56%
could easily be extended to allow
years to test a building's integrity

01:14:19.680 --> 01:14:22.780
and such an adjustment would
be perfectly legitimate

01:14:22.780 --> 01:14:26.390
as a standard feature
of Islamic law.

01:14:26.390 --> 01:14:29.000
We see the importance and
authenticity of this approach

01:14:29.000 --> 01:14:33.160
to Islamic law and in exchange
recorded by an old friend of mine

01:14:33.160 --> 01:14:35.220
on whom I actually will
my dissertation way back

01:14:35.220 --> 01:14:36.960
in the last century.

01:14:36.960 --> 01:14:40.160
The 13th century Egyptian jurist
of the [inaudible] school,

01:14:40.160 --> 01:14:43.860
Shihab al-Din al-Qarafi and I'm
translating here from the Arabic.

01:14:43.860 --> 01:14:48.590
Question, what is the correct view
regarding those rulings upheld

01:14:48.590 --> 01:14:53.150 position:56%
in the school of Maliki, Shafi'i and
the rest which have been deducted

01:14:53.150 --> 01:14:55.820
on the basis of habits
and customs prevailing

01:14:55.820 --> 01:14:59.900
at the time these jurists
reached these conclusions.

01:14:59.900 --> 01:15:02.890
When these customs change
and the practice comes

01:15:02.890 --> 01:15:07.070
to indicate the opposite of what it
used to, are the rulings recorded

01:15:07.070 --> 01:15:10.870
in the manuals of the jurists
rendered thereby defunct.

01:15:10.870 --> 01:15:15.670
It becoming incumbent to issue new
rulings based on the new custom

01:15:15.670 --> 01:15:18.920
or is it to be said we
are merely followers

01:15:18.920 --> 01:15:21.920
of the independent,
authoritative jurists.

01:15:21.920 --> 01:15:25.710
It is thus not our place
to innovate new rulings

01:15:25.710 --> 01:15:28.790
as we lack the qualifications
to do so.

01:15:28.790 --> 01:15:32.350
Therefore, we issue rulings
according to what we find

01:15:32.350 --> 01:15:34.830
in the books handed
down on the authority

01:15:34.830 --> 01:15:38.970
of the independent
authoritative jurists.

01:15:38.970 --> 01:15:44.040
Answer, holding to rulings that
have been deduced on the basis

01:15:44.040 --> 01:15:46.110
of prevailing customs even

01:15:46.110 --> 01:15:51.290
after these customs have changed is
a violation of unanimous consensus

01:15:51.290 --> 01:15:56.890
and an open display of ignorance
of the religion, end of quote.

01:15:56.890 --> 01:16:00.810
Again, almost every area of
Islamic law consists of rules

01:16:00.810 --> 01:16:05.510
that include an admixture of legal
interpretations on the one hand

01:16:05.510 --> 01:16:08.060
and factual assessments
on the other.

01:16:08.060 --> 01:16:12.070 position:56%
This includes rules in areas ranging
from family law to the status

01:16:12.070 --> 01:16:16.030
of non-Muslims, commercial
law, jihad and even aspects

01:16:16.030 --> 01:16:20.310
of the criminal law for example,
rules governing apostasy.

01:16:20.310 --> 01:16:22.700
In all of these areas
where the rules

01:16:22.700 --> 01:16:25.130
of the books reflect
the lived realities

01:16:25.130 --> 01:16:28.860
of pre-modern Muslim society
these rules can be adjusted

01:16:28.860 --> 01:16:33.500
to modern facts without in
any way violating the sanctity

01:16:33.500 --> 01:16:35.830
of Islamic law.

01:16:35.830 --> 01:16:37.130
Another major feature

01:16:37.130 --> 01:16:39.770
of the classical tradition
is its recognition

01:16:39.770 --> 01:16:42.480
of the limits of Islamic law.

01:16:42.480 --> 01:16:45.400
This is a difficult point
to make in a modern context

01:16:45.400 --> 01:16:50.700 position:56%
where secular is assumed to take
over where the religious leaves off.

01:16:50.700 --> 01:16:57.100
And secular is understood to
be the antithesis of religious.

01:16:57.100 --> 01:17:00.670
My point, however, is simply
that Islamic law recognized

01:17:00.670 --> 01:17:05.720
that the law itself was not
intended to address all issues.

01:17:05.720 --> 01:17:09.970
And that beyond the scope of the
source's jurisdiction other forms

01:17:09.970 --> 01:17:14.470
of deliberation, including those
that rely on reason, science,

01:17:14.470 --> 01:17:18.640
practical experience, even
perhaps spiritual epiphany could be

01:17:18.640 --> 01:17:20.640
legitimately invoked.

01:17:20.640 --> 01:17:23.360
To be sure this never
amounted to what we

01:17:23.360 --> 01:17:26.940
in the modern west would
identify as secular

01:17:26.940 --> 01:17:30.320
for Muslim jurists never
acknowledged the propriety

01:17:30.320 --> 01:17:34.300
or proceeding as if
God did not exist.

01:17:34.300 --> 01:17:36.140
They did recognize, however,

01:17:36.140 --> 01:17:40.750
that Islam as a religion is
broader in scope than sharia.

01:17:40.750 --> 01:17:43.740
And that the limits of
sharia do not, therefore,

01:17:43.740 --> 01:17:46.130
equal the limits of Islam.

01:17:46.130 --> 01:17:50.190
Thus, assuming that sharia did
not address an issue concretely an

01:17:50.190 --> 01:17:55.050
approach to that issue that
was grounded say in chemistry

01:17:55.050 --> 01:17:59.230
or actuarial science or plain old
mathematics could be perfectly

01:17:59.230 --> 01:18:05.130
Islamic even if it was not based
in sharia in the strict sense.

01:18:05.130 --> 01:18:10.100
This is the area for which I have
coined the term the Islamic secular

01:18:10.100 --> 01:18:13.030
rather than opposing
or even competing

01:18:13.030 --> 01:18:17.270
with sharia is simply
complement sharia by recognizing

01:18:17.270 --> 01:18:20.160
that in many instances
Muslims cannot rely

01:18:20.160 --> 01:18:22.590
on sharia for concrete answers.

01:18:22.590 --> 01:18:27.320
In fact, in any number of instances
their reasoning will be generically

01:18:27.320 --> 01:18:32.030
indistinguishable from that of
their non-Muslim compatriots.

01:18:32.030 --> 01:18:36.020
Take an issue for example,
such as speed limits

01:18:36.020 --> 01:18:42.090 position:56%
or licensing medical doctors, excuse
me or licensing medical doctors.

01:18:42.090 --> 01:18:45.800
The most sharia could provide here
would be the value of ensuring

01:18:45.800 --> 01:18:50.130
that such policies served the
communal interests of safety,

01:18:50.130 --> 01:18:52.310
competence, and the like.

01:18:52.310 --> 01:18:56.030
What actually constitutes
safety or competence, however,

01:18:56.030 --> 01:19:00.800
in concrete terms could not be
determined on the basis of sharia

01:19:00.800 --> 01:19:03.440
for there simply is
nothing in sharia

01:19:03.440 --> 01:19:08.650
that could identify 55 miles per
hour as an appropriate speed limit

01:19:08.650 --> 01:19:12.140
or three or four or
six years of rotation

01:19:12.140 --> 01:19:15.160
as a requirement for
medical licensing.

01:19:15.160 --> 01:19:19.190
Rather, in deliberating these
issues, Muslims would have to rely

01:19:19.190 --> 01:19:24.620 position:56%
on the same kinds of considerations
upon which non-Muslims rely physics,

01:19:24.620 --> 01:19:29.460
actuarial science, insurance
adjusters, experience and the like.

01:19:29.460 --> 01:19:33.490
And this would extend to a
virtually endless list of issues

01:19:33.490 --> 01:19:37.430
in the contemporary public
domain from immigration policy

01:19:37.430 --> 01:19:41.970
to national healthcare, from
FAA regulations to tenure

01:19:41.970 --> 01:19:45.290
and promotion procedures
in our universities.

01:19:45.290 --> 01:19:49.680
All of this is extremely
important for at least two reasons.

01:19:49.680 --> 01:19:53.650
First, precisely because
things such as speed limits

01:19:53.650 --> 01:19:55.610
or building occupancy codes

01:19:55.610 --> 01:19:59.220
or national healthcare plans
are not governed by sharia

01:19:59.220 --> 01:20:03.150
in the strict sense Muslims
and non-Muslims can be brought

01:20:03.150 --> 01:20:06.240
into conversation and
debate over these issues

01:20:06.240 --> 01:20:08.940
on a shared intellectual plane.

01:20:08.940 --> 01:20:14.940 position:56%
Sharia in other words, does not
constitute a barrier between Muslims

01:20:14.940 --> 01:20:18.330
and non-Muslims when it comes
to debating these issues.

01:20:18.330 --> 01:20:23.100
Second, because society is perhaps
more affected on a daily basis

01:20:23.100 --> 01:20:26.180
by regulations in the
non-sharia realm than it is

01:20:26.180 --> 01:20:30.420
by rules strictly dictated by
sharia, even in a polity governed

01:20:30.420 --> 01:20:34.510
by sharia the area of presumed
conflict between Muslims

01:20:34.510 --> 01:20:39.080
and non-Muslims might be much
narrower than is commonly presumed.

01:20:39.080 --> 01:20:41.230
And the area of what
John Rawls will refer

01:20:41.230 --> 01:20:46.680
to as public reason might be much
broader than is commonly assumed.

01:20:46.680 --> 01:20:50.730
Attention to the Islamic
secular is also important

01:20:50.730 --> 01:20:54.730
to the modern political order
of Muslim states for part

01:20:54.730 --> 01:20:58.380
of the problem here is the
tendency on the part of governments

01:20:58.380 --> 01:21:01.760
on the one hand and Islamist
movements on the other

01:21:01.760 --> 01:21:05.440
to invoke the unassailable
authority of sharia as a means

01:21:05.440 --> 01:21:06.870
of raising whatever rules

01:21:06.870 --> 01:21:10.570
or policies they propose
beyond critique.

01:21:10.570 --> 01:21:14.330
Careful attention to the Islamic
secular meanwhile could confer

01:21:14.330 --> 01:21:17.100
at least three distinct advantages.

01:21:17.100 --> 01:21:21.700
First, it could insulate Muslim
governments from inflated charges

01:21:21.700 --> 01:21:27.550 position:56%
of violating Islamic law every time
they institute economic, educational

01:21:27.550 --> 01:21:32.860
or bureaucratic policies that are
not explicitly dictated by sharia.

01:21:32.860 --> 01:21:35.900
Second, it could empower
Muslim communities

01:21:35.900 --> 01:21:39.460
to hold their governments to
greater degrees of accountability

01:21:39.460 --> 01:21:41.950
by denying these governments
the ability

01:21:41.950 --> 01:21:47.180 position:56%
to wrap their everyday policy in the
unassailable authority of sharia.

01:21:47.180 --> 01:21:52.090
Finally, it could contribute to
the domestication of power itself

01:21:52.090 --> 01:21:57.180 position:56%
by forcing power to negotiate its
right to coerce rather than assuming

01:21:57.180 --> 01:22:00.950
that Muslim rulers in governments
have some uncontested right

01:22:00.950 --> 01:22:03.130
to coerce in the name
of what a friend

01:22:03.130 --> 01:22:06.150
of mine would call
God's pious dictator.

01:22:06.150 --> 01:22:12.700 position:56%
I would like to end these incomplete
ruminations on reform in Islamic law

01:22:12.700 --> 01:22:16.480
by referring to what remains in
my mind an outstanding problem.

01:22:16.480 --> 01:22:17.780
And I'd like to take advantage

01:22:17.780 --> 01:22:21.000
of the intellectual
[inaudible] room underscored.

01:22:21.000 --> 01:22:24.170
The problem of which I am
speaking is quite simply history.

01:22:24.170 --> 01:22:31.210
More specifically, unlike modern
states Islamic law never devised a

01:22:31.210 --> 01:22:35.340
mechanism for wiping the
books clean of outmoded,

01:22:35.340 --> 01:22:38.200
discarded or discredited rules.

01:22:38.200 --> 01:22:42.690
Rather, juristic culture as
a whole oversaw this process

01:22:42.690 --> 01:22:44.640
